{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":992,"text":"This year, Germany is celebrating"},{"time":2470,"text":"the 25th anniversary of the peaceful revolution"},{"time":5556,"text":"in East Germany."},{"time":7092,"text":"In 1989, the Communist regime was moved away,"},{"time":11858,"text":"the Berlin Wall came down, and one year later,"},{"time":15320,"text":"the German Democratic Republic, the GDR,"},{"time":19485,"text":"in the East was unified"},{"time":21154,"text":"with the Federal Republic of Germany in the West"},{"time":23844,"text":"to found today's Germany."},{"time":27117,"text":"Among many other things, Germany inherited"},{"time":30511,"text":"the archives of the East German secret police,"},{"time":35104,"text":"known as the Stasi."},{"time":38420,"text":"Only two years after its dissolution,"},{"time":40960,"text":"its documents were opened to the public,"},{"time":44602,"text":"and historians such as me started"},{"time":47677,"text":"to study these documents"},{"time":49105,"text":"to learn more about how the GDR surveillance state"},{"time":53797,"text":"functioned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55507,"text":"Perhaps you have watched the movie"},{"time":58303,"text":"\"The Lives of Others.\""},{"time":60341,"text":"This movie made the Stasi known worldwide,"},{"time":65092,"text":"and as we live in an age where words"},{"time":67942,"text":"such as \"surveillance\" or \"wiretapping\""},{"time":71229,"text":"are on the front pages of newspapers,"},{"time":73979,"text":"I would like to speak about how the Stasi"},{"time":76802,"text":"really worked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79201,"text":"At the beginning, let's have a short look"},{"time":81970,"text":"at the history of the Stasi,"},{"time":83928,"text":"because it's really important for understanding"},{"time":86219,"text":"its self-conception."},{"time":89706,"text":"Its origins are located in Russia."},{"time":92418,"text":"In 1917, the Russian Communists founded"},{"time":94736,"text":"the Emergency Commission for Combating"},{"time":96930,"text":"Counter-Revolution and Sabotage,"},{"time":99731,"text":"shortly Cheka."},{"time":101950,"text":"It was led by Felix Dzerzhinsky."},{"time":104960,"text":"The Cheka was an instrument of the Communists"},{"time":108203,"text":"to establish their regime by terrorizing the population"},{"time":111960,"text":"and executing their enemies."},{"time":114435,"text":"It evolved later into the well-known KGB."},{"time":120244,"text":"The Cheka was the idol of the Stasi officers."},{"time":123750,"text":"They called themselves Chekists,"},{"time":126822,"text":"and even the emblem was very similar,"},{"time":129680,"text":"as you can see here."},{"time":132661,"text":"In fact, the secret police of Russia"},{"time":136227,"text":"was the creator and instructor of the Stasi."},{"time":139518,"text":"When the Red Army occupied East Germany in 1945,"},{"time":143109,"text":"it immediately expanded there,"},{"time":145497,"text":"and soon it started to train the German Communists"},{"time":149118,"text":"to build up their own secret police."},{"time":152366,"text":"By the way, in this hall where we are now,"},{"time":155886,"text":"the ruling party of the GDR was founded in 1946."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161566,"text":"Five years later, the Stasi was established,"},{"time":164950,"text":"and step by step, the dirty job of oppression"},{"time":167569,"text":"was handed over to it."},{"time":170111,"text":"For instance, the central jail"},{"time":172542,"text":"for political prisoners,"},{"time":173856,"text":"which was established by the Russians,"},{"time":176604,"text":"was taken over by the Stasi"},{"time":178864,"text":"and used until the end of Communism."},{"time":182048,"text":"You see it here."},{"time":183850,"text":"At the beginning, every important step"},{"time":187485,"text":"took place under the attendance of the Russians."},{"time":191040,"text":"But the Germans are known to be very effective,"},{"time":194141,"text":"so the Stasi grew very quickly,"},{"time":197519,"text":"and already in 1953, it had more employees"},{"time":201207,"text":"than the Gestapo had,"},{"time":202905,"text":"the secret police of Nazi Germany."},{"time":205695,"text":"The number doubled in each decade."},{"time":208133,"text":"In 1989, more than 90,000 employees"},{"time":211558,"text":"worked for the Stasi."},{"time":213223,"text":"This meant that one employee"},{"time":215597,"text":"was responsible for 180 inhabitants,"},{"time":218810,"text":"which was really unique in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222809,"text":"At the top of this tremendous apparatus,"},{"time":225405,"text":"there was one man, Erich Mielke."},{"time":229189,"text":"He ruled the Ministry of State Security"},{"time":231450,"text":"for more than 30 years."},{"time":233769,"text":"He was a scrupulous functionary —"},{"time":236400,"text":"in his past, he killed two policemen"},{"time":239122,"text":"not far away from here —"},{"time":241130,"text":"who in fact personalized the Stasi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245197,"text":"But what was so exceptional about the Stasi?"},{"time":249690,"text":"Foremost, it was its enormous power,"},{"time":252600,"text":"because it united different functions"},{"time":256090,"text":"in one organization."},{"time":258365,"text":"First of all, the Stasi"},{"time":260476,"text":"was an intelligence service."},{"time":263571,"text":"It used all the imaginable instruments"},{"time":266050,"text":"for getting information secretly,"},{"time":268333,"text":"such as informers, or tapping phones,"},{"time":271934,"text":"as you can see it on the picture here."},{"time":274802,"text":"And it was not only active in East Germany,"},{"time":277806,"text":"but all over the world."},{"time":280543,"text":"Secondly, the Stasi was a secret police."},{"time":284506,"text":"It could stop people on the street"},{"time":286650,"text":"and arrest them in its own prisons."},{"time":291078,"text":"Thirdly, the Stasi worked"},{"time":292580,"text":"as a kind of public prosecutor."},{"time":295435,"text":"It had the right to open preliminary investigations"},{"time":298565,"text":"and to interrogate people officially."},{"time":302262,"text":"Last but not least,"},{"time":304353,"text":"the Stasi had its own armed forces."},{"time":308218,"text":"More than 11,000 soldiers were serving"},{"time":310222,"text":"in its so-called Guards Regiment."},{"time":313732,"text":"It was founded to crash down protests and uprisings."},{"time":318148,"text":"Due to this concentration of power,"},{"time":320875,"text":"the Stasi was called a state in the state."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325940,"text":"But let's look in more and more detail"},{"time":328199,"text":"at the tools of the Stasi."},{"time":330816,"text":"Please keep in mind that at that time"},{"time":332459,"text":"the web and smartphones were not yet invented."},{"time":336284,"text":"Of course, the Stasi used all kinds"},{"time":339525,"text":"of technical instruments to survey people."},{"time":342598,"text":"Telephones were wiretapped,"},{"time":344711,"text":"including the phone of the\nGerman chancellor in the West,"},{"time":348850,"text":"and often also the apartments."},{"time":351802,"text":"Every day, 90,000 letters were being opened"},{"time":355195,"text":"by these machines."},{"time":358541,"text":"The Stasi also shadowed\ntens of thousands of people"},{"time":362239,"text":"using specially trained agents and secret cameras"},{"time":365471,"text":"to document every step one took."},{"time":369006,"text":"In this picture, you can see me"},{"time":371674,"text":"as a young man just in front of this building"},{"time":375154,"text":"where we are now, photographed by a Stasi agent."},{"time":378908,"text":"The Stasi even collected the smell of people."},{"time":383304,"text":"It stored samples of it in closed jars"},{"time":386563,"text":"which were found after the peaceful revolution."},{"time":391022,"text":"For all these tasks, highly specialized departments"},{"time":395258,"text":"were responsible."},{"time":397626,"text":"The one which was tapping phone calls"},{"time":399806,"text":"was completely separated"},{"time":401696,"text":"from the one which controlled the letters,"},{"time":404242,"text":"for good reasons,"},{"time":405540,"text":"because if one agent quit the Stasi,"},{"time":410217,"text":"his knowledge was very small."},{"time":412131,"text":"Contrast that with Snowden, for example."},{"time":416119,"text":"But the vertical specialization was also important"},{"time":419196,"text":"to prevent all kinds of empathy"},{"time":421501,"text":"with the object of observation."},{"time":424496,"text":"The agent who shadowed me"},{"time":426800,"text":"didn't know who I was"},{"time":428657,"text":"or why I was surveyed."},{"time":430522,"text":"In fact, I smuggled forbidden books"},{"time":432136,"text":"from West to East Germany."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435028,"text":"But what was even more typical for the Stasi"},{"time":438220,"text":"was the use of human intelligence,"},{"time":441384,"text":"people who reported secretly to the Stasi."},{"time":445577,"text":"For the Minister of State Security,"},{"time":447379,"text":"these so-called unofficial employees"},{"time":450291,"text":"were the most important tools."},{"time":453186,"text":"From 1975 on, nearly 200,000 people"},{"time":458509,"text":"collaborated constantly with the Stasi,"},{"time":461346,"text":"more than one percent of the population."},{"time":466222,"text":"And in a way, the minister was right,"},{"time":468950,"text":"because technical instruments"},{"time":470891,"text":"can only register what people are doing,"},{"time":474463,"text":"but agents and spies can also report"},{"time":477771,"text":"what people are planning to do"},{"time":479474,"text":"and what they are thinking."},{"time":481834,"text":"Therefore, the Stasi recruited so many informants."},{"time":486615,"text":"The system of how to get them"},{"time":489459,"text":"and how to educate them, as it was called,"},{"time":492491,"text":"was very sophisticated."},{"time":495181,"text":"The Stasi had its own university,"},{"time":498088,"text":"not far away from here,"},{"time":499608,"text":"where the methods were explored"},{"time":501535,"text":"and taught to the officers."},{"time":504204,"text":"This guideline gave a detailed description"},{"time":507955,"text":"of every step you have to take"},{"time":510578,"text":"if you want to convince human beings"},{"time":512940,"text":"to betray their fellow citizens."},{"time":516920,"text":"Sometimes it's said that informants were pressured"},{"time":520264,"text":"to becoming one,"},{"time":521720,"text":"but that's mostly not true,"},{"time":524314,"text":"because a forced informant is a bad informant."},{"time":528225,"text":"Only someone who wants to give\nyou the information you need"},{"time":531312,"text":"is an effective whistleblower."},{"time":533973,"text":"The main reasons why people\ncooperated with the Stasi"},{"time":538830,"text":"were political conviction and material benefits."},{"time":544330,"text":"The officers also tried to create a personal bond"},{"time":547440,"text":"between themselves and the informant,"},{"time":550848,"text":"and to be honest, the example of the Stasi shows"},{"time":556000,"text":"that it's not so difficult to win someone"},{"time":559392,"text":"in order to betray others."},{"time":562835,"text":"Even some of the top dissidents in East Germany"},{"time":566586,"text":"collaborated with the Stasi,"},{"time":568421,"text":"as for instance Ibrahim Böhme."},{"time":572166,"text":"In 1989, he was the leader of the peaceful revolution"},{"time":574956,"text":"and he nearly became the first freely\nelected Prime Minister of the GDR"},{"time":579330,"text":"until it came out that he was an informant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584475,"text":"The net of spies was really broad."},{"time":588404,"text":"In nearly every institution,"},{"time":590110,"text":"even in the churches or in West Germany,"},{"time":593355,"text":"there were many of them."},{"time":595543,"text":"I remember telling a leading Stasi officer,"},{"time":599032,"text":"\"If you had sent an informant to me,"},{"time":602461,"text":"I would surely have recognized him.\""},{"time":605091,"text":"His answer was,"},{"time":606950,"text":"\"We didn't send anyone."},{"time":608393,"text":"We took those who were around you.\""},{"time":611415,"text":"And in fact, two of my best friends"},{"time":614070,"text":"reported about me to the Stasi."},{"time":618401,"text":"Not only in my case, informers were very close."},{"time":620990,"text":"For example, Vera Lengsfeld,\nanother leading dissident,"},{"time":624693,"text":"in her case it was her husband who spied on her."},{"time":628906,"text":"A famous writer was betrayed by his brother."},{"time":632259,"text":"This reminds me of the novel \"1984\" by George Orwell,"},{"time":636151,"text":"where the only apparently trustable person"},{"time":639230,"text":"was an informer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642043,"text":"But why did the Stasi collect all this information"},{"time":645740,"text":"in its archives?"},{"time":647661,"text":"The main purpose was to control the society."},{"time":651720,"text":"In nearly every speech, the Stasi minister"},{"time":654303,"text":"gave the order to find out who is who,"},{"time":657025,"text":"which meant who thinks what."},{"time":660119,"text":"He didn't want to wait until somebody"},{"time":661870,"text":"tried to act against the regime."},{"time":664390,"text":"He wanted to know in advance"},{"time":666280,"text":"what people were thinking and planning."},{"time":669175,"text":"The East Germans knew, of course,"},{"time":671997,"text":"that they were surrounded by informers,"},{"time":675167,"text":"in a totalitarian regime that created mistrust"},{"time":679140,"text":"and a state of widespread fear,"},{"time":682234,"text":"the most important tools to oppress people"},{"time":685750,"text":"in any dictatorship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687909,"text":"That's why not many East Germans tried"},{"time":690512,"text":"to fight against the Communist regime."},{"time":694796,"text":"If yes, the Stasi often used a method"},{"time":699378,"text":"which was really diabolic."},{"time":702050,"text":"It was called Zersetzung,"},{"time":704236,"text":"and it's described in another guideline."},{"time":707907,"text":"The word is difficult to translate because it means"},{"time":710707,"text":"originally \"biodegradation.\""},{"time":714605,"text":"But actually, it's a quite accurate description."},{"time":717959,"text":"The goal was to destroy secretly"},{"time":721518,"text":"the self-confidence of people,"},{"time":724408,"text":"for example by damaging their reputation,"},{"time":727521,"text":"by organizing failures in their work,"},{"time":730990,"text":"and by destroying their personal relationships."},{"time":735620,"text":"Considering this, East Germany\nwas a very modern dictatorship."},{"time":740995,"text":"The Stasi didn't try to arrest every dissident."},{"time":745366,"text":"It preferred to paralyze them,"},{"time":748457,"text":"and it could do so because"},{"time":750960,"text":"it had access to so much personal information"},{"time":754310,"text":"and to so many institutions."},{"time":758240,"text":"Detaining someone was used only"},{"time":760512,"text":"as a last resort."},{"time":763042,"text":"For this, the Stasi owned 17 remand prisons,"},{"time":766347,"text":"one in every district."},{"time":768864,"text":"Here, the Stasi also developed"},{"time":771538,"text":"quite modern methods of detention."},{"time":775980,"text":"Normally, the interrogation officer"},{"time":777763,"text":"didn't torture the prisoner."},{"time":781226,"text":"Instead, he used a sophisticated system"},{"time":783802,"text":"of psychological pressure"},{"time":785940,"text":"in which strict isolation was central."},{"time":790034,"text":"Nearly no prisoner resisted"},{"time":792318,"text":"without giving a testimony."},{"time":795547,"text":"If you have the occasion,"},{"time":797609,"text":"do visit the former Stasi prison in Berlin"},{"time":801060,"text":"and attend a guided tour\nwith a former political prisoner"},{"time":804649,"text":"who will explain to you how this worked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807505,"text":"One more question needs to be answered:"},{"time":810664,"text":"If the Stasi were so well organized,"},{"time":813106,"text":"why did the Communist regime collapse?"},{"time":817439,"text":"First, in 1989, the leadership in East Germany"},{"time":821570,"text":"was uncertain what to do against"},{"time":823831,"text":"the growing protest of people."},{"time":826768,"text":"It was especially confused"},{"time":829119,"text":"because in the mother country of socialism,"},{"time":831890,"text":"the Soviet Union,"},{"time":833410,"text":"a more liberal policy took place."},{"time":836793,"text":"In addition, the regime was dependent"},{"time":839210,"text":"on the loans from the West."},{"time":842602,"text":"Therefore, no order to crash down the uprising"},{"time":845150,"text":"was given to the Stasi."},{"time":848227,"text":"Secondly, in the Communist ideology,"},{"time":851860,"text":"there's no place for criticism."},{"time":854513,"text":"Instead, the leadership stuck to the belief"},{"time":856820,"text":"that socialism is a perfect system,"},{"time":859614,"text":"and the Stasi had to confirm that, of course."},{"time":863865,"text":"The consequence was"},{"time":866226,"text":"that despite all the information,"},{"time":868722,"text":"the regime couldn't analyze its real problems,"},{"time":872886,"text":"and therefore it couldn't solve them."},{"time":875571,"text":"In the end, the Stasi died"},{"time":878275,"text":"because of the structures"},{"time":880068,"text":"that it was charged with protecting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883788,"text":"The ending of the Stasi"},{"time":885858,"text":"was something tragic,"},{"time":887905,"text":"because these officers"},{"time":889964,"text":"were kept busy during the peaceful revolution"},{"time":893032,"text":"with only one thing:"},{"time":895007,"text":"to destroy the documents"},{"time":897660,"text":"they had produced during decades."},{"time":901351,"text":"Fortunately,"},{"time":903269,"text":"they had been stopped by human rights activists."},{"time":906806,"text":"That's why today we can use the files"},{"time":909732,"text":"to get a better understanding"},{"time":911356,"text":"of how a surveillance state functions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":914136,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916133,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":924518,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Thank you. Thank you very much."},{"time":930578,"text":"So Hubertus, I want to ask you a couple of questions"},{"time":933302,"text":"because I have here Der Spiegel from last week."},{"time":936090,"text":"\"Mein Nachbar NSA.\" My neighbor, the NSA."},{"time":940964,"text":"And you just told us about my neighbor,"},{"time":943595,"text":"the spies and the informant from East Germany."},{"time":946583,"text":"So there is a direct link between these two stories"},{"time":949283,"text":"or there isn't?"},{"time":951161,"text":"What's your reaction as a\nhistorian when you see this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":953183,"text":"Hubertus Knabe: I think there are"},{"time":954908,"text":"several aspects to mention."},{"time":956811,"text":"At first, I think there's a difference"},{"time":959877,"text":"of why you are collecting this data."},{"time":963965,"text":"Are you doing that for protecting your people"},{"time":966283,"text":"against terrorist attacks,"},{"time":967830,"text":"or are you doing that for oppressing your people?"},{"time":970600,"text":"So that makes a fundamental difference."},{"time":972542,"text":"But on the other hand,"},{"time":974891,"text":"also in a democracy, these\ninstruments can be abused,"},{"time":979210,"text":"and that is something where we really have"},{"time":981376,"text":"to be aware to stop that,"},{"time":982761,"text":"and that also the intelligence services"},{"time":985634,"text":"are respecting the rules we have."},{"time":988755,"text":"The third point, probably,"},{"time":990255,"text":"we really can be happy that we live in a democracy,"},{"time":993543,"text":"because you can be sure that Russia and China"},{"time":997223,"text":"are doing the same,"},{"time":998755,"text":"but nobody speaks about that"},{"time":1000321,"text":"because nobody could do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002612,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009398,"text":"BG: When the story came out first,"},{"time":1011451,"text":"last July, last year,"},{"time":1013646,"text":"you filed a criminal complaint"},{"time":1016474,"text":"with a German tribunal. Why?"},{"time":1019454,"text":"HK: Yeah, I did so because of\nthe second point I mentioned,"},{"time":1022667,"text":"that I think especially in a democracy,"},{"time":1025564,"text":"the rules are for everybody."},{"time":1029022,"text":"They are made for everybody, so it's not allowed"},{"time":1031386,"text":"that any institution doesn't respect the rules."},{"time":1035177,"text":"In the criminal code of Germany, it's written"},{"time":1037155,"text":"that it's not allowed to tap somebody"},{"time":1039010,"text":"without the permission of the judge."},{"time":1041398,"text":"Fortunately, it's written in\nthe criminal code of Germany,"},{"time":1045219,"text":"so if it's not respected, then I think"},{"time":1049150,"text":"an investigation is necessary,"},{"time":1051046,"text":"and it took a very long time that"},{"time":1053025,"text":"the public prosecutor of Germany started this,"},{"time":1055131,"text":"and he started it only in the case of Angela Merkel,"},{"time":1058702,"text":"and not in the case of all the\nother people living in Germany."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1061658,"text":"BG: That doesn't surprise me because —"},{"time":1064131,"text":"(Applause) —"},{"time":1066254,"text":"because of the story you told."},{"time":1069697,"text":"Seen from the outside, I live outside of Germany,"},{"time":1072180,"text":"and I expected the Germans to react"},{"time":1073957,"text":"much more strongly, immediately."},{"time":1077177,"text":"And instead, the reaction really came only"},{"time":1079789,"text":"when Chancellor Merkel was revealed"},{"time":1081646,"text":"as being wiretapped. Why so?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085201,"text":"HK: I take it as a good sign,"},{"time":1087064,"text":"because people feel secure in this democracy."},{"time":1091394,"text":"They aren't afraid that they will be arrested,"},{"time":1093608,"text":"and if you leave this hall after the conference,"},{"time":1096771,"text":"nobody has to be afraid that the secret police"},{"time":1099335,"text":"is standing out and is arresting you."},{"time":1101773,"text":"So that's a good sign, I think."},{"time":1103367,"text":"People are not really scared, as they could be."},{"time":1106242,"text":"But of course, I think, the institutions"},{"time":1110596,"text":"are responsible to stop illegal actions"},{"time":1113163,"text":"in Germany or wherever they happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1116281,"text":"BG: A personal question,\nand this is the last one."},{"time":1119474,"text":"There has been a debate in Germany about"},{"time":1121740,"text":"granting asylum to Edward Snowden."},{"time":1123281,"text":"Would you be in favor or against?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1126046,"text":"HK: Oh, that's a difficult question,"},{"time":1127734,"text":"but if you ask me,"},{"time":1129420,"text":"and if I answer honestly,"},{"time":1131075,"text":"I would give him the asylum,"},{"time":1132841,"text":"because I think it was really brave what he did,"},{"time":1134890,"text":"and he destroyed his whole life"},{"time":1137502,"text":"and his family and everything."},{"time":1139171,"text":"So I think, for these people,\nwe should do something,"},{"time":1142380,"text":"and especially if you see the German history,"},{"time":1146534,"text":"where so many people had to escape"},{"time":1149031,"text":"and they asked for asylum in other countries"},{"time":1151347,"text":"and they didn't get it,"},{"time":1152730,"text":"so it would be a good sign to give him asylum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1155567,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1157378,"text":"BG: Hubertus, thank you very much."}]}]}